subSection.paragraph:
Our molecular matrix consisted of 1.548 aligned base pairs (bp) of COI, with 392 variable sites and 184 parsimonyinformative sites. Although we solely utilized COI mitochondrial data, this gene serves as a robust mitochondrial marker for systematic investigations in social wasps (
Menezes et al . 2023
) and has been recently employed for species delimitation of Epiponini wasps (
Somavilla et al . 2021b
;
Barroso et al . 2022
). Our morphological dataset comprised 22 characters, including 14 binary characters and eight multi-state characters—one of which is additive (character 2). The characters 1–13 and 14–20 corresponded to female and male adults, respectively, while characters 21–23 pertained to nest architecture (adapted from Andena & Carpenter 2012 ). The characters 1–20 were newly proposed in this study.
